Description: The unique numeric code for the state. More information on state codes can be found [here](https://www23.statcan.gc.ca/imdb/p3VD.pl?Function=getVD&TVD=53971).
The unique numeric code for the county. More information on county codes can be found [here](https://www2.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial/2010/partners/pdf/FIPS_StateCounty_Code.pdf).
Code identifying a specific census tract. More information on tract codes can be found [here](https://transition.fcc.gov/form477/Geo/more_about_census_tracts.pdf).
Combined state, county, and tract identifier.
The full name of the census area.
Percentage of households using child care services.
Percentage of restaurants classified as fast food.
Percentage of population over 65 years old.
Percentage of households in the working class.
